# Localization Rule

When you add **any new user-facing text** in English to this app:

1. **Add the key to `en.json`** first with the English value.
2. **Add the same key to every other language file** in `Capybara_Rescue_App/Localizable/`:
   - tr.json, es-MX.json, pt-BR.json, zh-Hant.json, ja.json, hi.json, ar.json, id.json, ko.json, ms.json
3. **Use `L("key")`** in the Swift code instead of hardcoded strings.
4. **Add `@ObservedObject private var localizationManager = LocalizationManager.shared`** to views that display localized text so the UI updates when the user changes language.

Key naming: `section.name` (e.g. `settings.title`, `menu.food`, `common.cancel`).

See `LOCALIZATION.md` for the full guide.
